<br>
The whole point behind my poll was merely to make people stop and think.<br>
<br>
I don’t think anyone has any clear cut answers here, I sure don’t, but I was curious about what you all thought.<br>
<br>
If the poll and following posts made you angry, challenged your view, or in any other way made you inform yourself about the situation in Iraq, and the world itself, then I consider my mission accomplished..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Personally I have learned a great deal from this, for example I didn’t know the PNAC existed, thanks Kron. And, I didn’t know how some of you guys in the armed forces felt about this either. Taranna had a load of facts I found myself checking out as well hehe.<br>
<br>
The poll in itself didn’t tell us all that much, Altaris pointed out a great flaw in it early on, the fact that we don’t know how many euros voted. All the same, it did tell us that roughly 35% of this community either agree with Bush's policy, or trust his decision, and about the same number don’t.<br>
<br>
With that said, I share many of the sentiments that Xorthar has, and that’s not built on a hatred towards the US, but a general fear of the current foreign policy.<br>
<br>
Also, I don’t think we can dismiss the lessons history teaches us, or let it cloud our decision. <br>
<br>
The next few days will give us some answers, so maybe this thread will harden even more, or die out, I don’t know.<br>
<br>
Please be considerate when you post though, when you start bad mouthing someone the debate is already lost. <br>
